    "projects.0.title": "Smart Sensors for Urban Streams",
    "projects.0.desc": "Smart sensors installed in urban streams monitor pollution levels, water flow, and rainfall in real time. They issue early warnings to nearby communities and authorities, enabling the prevention of environmental emergencies and supporting timely decision-making to protect the surrounding ecosystem.",
    "projects.1.title": "Smart & Conscious Bus Shelters",
    "projects.1.desc": "Smart bus shelters equipped with LED lighting, solar panels, a micro wind turbine, charging stations, and a filtered water fountain for pets. Adaptable to each urban context, they provide sustainable and safe solutions for waiting for public transport while enhancing the overall citizen experience.",
    "projects.2.title": "Aerial Mobility eVOLTs",
    "projects.2.desc": "The future of urban mobility is already a reality with eVolts: piloted, 100% electric flying vehicles that operate at mid-level altitudes over strategic areas of the city. Designed primarily for short-distance travel, they provide agile and efficient response capabilities in emergency situations.",
    "projects.3.title": "Conscious Pedestrian Crossings",
    "projects.3.desc": "Smart pedestrian crossings that prioritize human life through LED technology, motion sensors, AI-powered cameras, and advanced signaling systems. They ensure safe passage for pedestrians, including children, older adults, and pets, adapting to their pace and specific needs within urban environments.",
    "projects.4.title":"Autonomous Monorails For Hillsides And Slopes",
    "projects.4.desc": "Small, electric, and autonomous last-mile monorails enable people living on hillsides or in hard-to-reach areas to move safely, comfortably, and sustainably. This solution improves connectivity to public transportation and reduces mobility barriers, particularly in vulnerable communities.",
