    "projects.6.desc":"Collective urban gardens co-managed by citizens promote the local production of fresh food and collaborative work. Harvested produce is distributed fairly among participants, strengthening social bonds and fostering a more conscious relationship with the natural environment.",
    "projects.7.title":"Human-Centered Urban Furniture",
    "projects.7.desc":"Smart urban furniture integrates climate and air quality sensors, Wi-Fi connectivity, solar-powered charging ports, and interactive systems such as voice or screen-based civic recommendations. It enhances the public space experience while promoting more connected, responsive, and sustainable urban environments.",
    "projects.8.title":"Green Walls And Sensory Art",
    "projects.8.desc":"Walls filled with life, color, vegetation, and collaborative art transform the urban landscape. Their maintenance is shared among neighbors and community sponsors. They incorporate mobile or modular vertical gardens that can be temporarily installed in grey or underutilized urban spaces, activating the environment and strengthening community ownership.",
    "projects.9.title":"Autonomous Robotaxis",
    "projects.9.desc":"A system of electric and autonomous vehicles connecting strategic points through short, flat, and direct routes. An efficient and sustainable solution for daily transportation, reducing congestion and improving accessibility within urban environments.",
    "projects.10.title":"Occupancy And Vehicle Couting Sensors",
    "projects.10.desc":"Occupancy sensors detect available parking spaces in real time at key locations across the city. This data is integrated into digital platforms to guide drivers, reduce traffic congestion, optimize the use of public space, and enhance the overall urban mobility experience.",
    "projects.11.title":"Intelligent Traffic Classifiers",
    "projects.11.desc":"A vehicle classification system using intelligent gantries that identify and organize traffic flow according to vehicle type. This technology enhances road safety and optimizes urban mobility by reducing congestion and improving roadway space management.",
    "projects.12.title":"Circular Economy Hubs",
    "projects.12.desc":"Small urban community exchange points where people can leave or take useful items such as clothing, books, food, plants, and other goods. They promote the circular economy, solidarity, and resource optimization, strengthening social ties and environmental awareness within each neighborhood.",
    "projects.13.title":"Citizen Governance Hubs",
    "projects.13.desc":"Citizen consultation and participation points where the community can access information about active local projects, vote on priorities, propose ideas, and track the progress of neighborhood initiatives. They foster transparency, shared responsibility, and collective empowerment in urban transformation processes.",
    "projects.14.title":"Calm And Relaxation Urban Pods",
    "projects.14.desc":"Soundproof cabins installed in urban environments to reduce noise, stimulation, and sensory overload. They function as calm oases within the fast pace of the city, offering a dedicated space for pause, reflection, and well-being—allowing individuals to disconnect from external pressures and reconnect with themselves.",
    "projects.15.title":"Living And Collaborative Eco-Roofs",
    "projects.15.desc":"Building rooftops are transformed into active spaces featuring urban farming, solar panels, and green rest areas. This activation promotes sustainability, energy self-sufficiency, and well-being. Underutilized surfaces are reimagined to generate environmental and social value within the urban fabric.",
    "projects.16.title":"Citizen Reporting App",
    "projects.16.desc":"A secure platform for registering citizen alerts with collective verification and immediate routing to relevant authorities or community networks. It enables the reporting of incidents such as theft, domestic violence, kidnapping, sexual abuse, excessive noise, animal mistreatment, and other public safety concerns—strengthening civic participation, accountability, and coordinated community response.",
    "projects.17.title":"AI Tourism And Civic Agents",
    "projects.17.desc":"An AI-powered conversational assistant trained on local data that provides immediate, clear, and up-to-date responses about directions, administrative procedures, public services, and other civic inquiries. It simplifies access to information and fosters a closer, more responsive relationship between citizens and their urban environment.",
    "projects.18.title":"Civic Listening Points",
    "projects.18.desc":"Public devices equipped with cameras and microphones collect citizens’ ideas, thoughts, and reflections in video and audio format. These inputs help build a collective memory of the city’s emotions and experiences, strengthening large-scale listening, civic participation, and the connection between people and their urban territory.",
    "projects.19.title":"Smart Traffic Lights And Crossings",
    "projects.19.desc":"Truly intelligent traffic lights that adjust their timing based on real-time pedestrian and vehicle flow. Using AI-powered cameras integrated into the existing traffic signal network, they enhance mobility, reduce waiting times, and prioritize the safety of all road users.",
    "projects.20.title":"Collective Library Network",
    "projects.20.desc":"Small boxes or modules where people can freely take, leave, or exchange books. They promote reading, community sharing, and a sense of ownership over public space. With minimal investment, they activate waiting or transit areas, fostering trust, culture, and collective care within the urban environment.",
    "projects.21.title":"Anti-Noise Patrol Dones",
    "projects.21.desc":"Civic drones respond to citizen reports using onboard cameras and loudspeakers to broadcast messages when necessary. They conduct environmental monitoring routes—detecting issues such as waste accumulation, excessive noise, or fire risks—and promote respect for the urban environment through active civic presence and rapid response, rather than traditional policing.",
    "projects.22.title":"Smart Waste Collection Sensors",
    "projects.22.desc":"Smart sensors monitor bin fill levels and conditions in real time, enabling optimized collection routes, reduced operational costs, and lower emissions. Integrated with digital platforms, they improve efficiency, cleanliness, and environmental performance while supporting data-driven and sustainable waste management across the city.",
    "projects.23.title":"Regenerative Streetscapes",
    "projects.23.desc":"Regenerative Streetscapes transform urban corridors into living infrastructure that restores ecological balance and enhances social life. By integrating green stormwater systems, native vegetation, permeable surfaces, and pedestrian-first design, streets reduce heat, manage water naturally, and create healthier, climate-resilient public spaces.",

